<h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">Setting Up a Scrabble Game — Board, Tiles & Racks Guide</h1>
<p class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mb-6">Published June 15, 2026 · 4 min read</p>

<p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mb-8">Getting a Scrabble game started correctly takes less than 2 minutes once you know the steps. From placing the board to drawing your first tiles, this guide covers everything you need for a properly set-up game — whether it's your first time or you need a quick refresher on the official rules.</p>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">What You Need</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
  <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
    <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">1</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">15×15 game board</p></div>
    <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">100</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Letter tiles</p></div>
    <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">2-4</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Tile racks</p></div>
    <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">1</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Tile bag</p></div>
  </div>
</div>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Step-by-Step Setup</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/10">
  <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-purple-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">🧩 Setup Process</p>
  <div class="space-y-3">
    <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
      <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">1</span>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-300">Place the board on a flat surface with all players able to reach comfortably. Ensure the centre star square is visible to everyone.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
      <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">2</span>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-300">Put all 100 tiles face-down into the tile bag. Shake or mix thoroughly so tiles are randomly distributed.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
      <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">3</span>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-300">Give each player a tile rack. Place racks so other players cannot see your tiles.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
      <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">4</span>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-300">Determine who goes first: each player draws 1 tile — closest to A starts (blanks beat all letters). Return tiles to bag.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
      <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">5</span>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-300">Each player draws 7 tiles from the bag and places them on their rack. Don't show other players! You're ready to begin.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Tile Distribution</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
    <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-2">Most Common Tiles</p>
    <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">E×12, A×9, I×9, O×8, N×6, R×6, T×6, L×4, S×4, U×4</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-red-500/30 bg-red-950/10">
    <p class="text-red-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-2">Rarest Tiles (1 each)</p>
    <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Q(10pts), Z(10pts), X(8pts), J(8pts), K(5pts) + 2 Blanks(0pts)</p>
  </div>
</div>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Common Setup Mistakes</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Not mixing tiles enough:</span> Give the bag a good 10-second shake. Tiles tend to settle in layers — if you just reach in, you may get letter clusters from manufacturing.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Forgetting the centre rule:</span> The first word MUST cover the centre star square. Many beginners place their first word anywhere — this is invalid and earns no double-word bonus.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Wrong tile count:</span> Always verify you have exactly 100 tiles before starting. Missing tiles (often blanks or S tiles) completely change game balance.</p>
  </div>
</div>

